content.description: Project line that I haven't messed with a whole lot yet, so the grade is a total guess. Sit start (?) moving up to the horn corner of the lip and traverse to the jug holds near the middle of the lip and top out same as "perspective."
content.protection: Several pads, or a spotter moving a pad as you traverse.
content.location: Starts on the far right side of the boulder. Stand start is pretty mellow, but a sit looks doable.

content.description: Super fun lip traverse line! Amazing texture and neat holds make this heel hook heavy line a must check out kinda line. Crux is toping out from the jug hold to the uber blank slab top. Good luck!
content.protection: Several pads is ideal, but not necessary if your spotter can keep moving the pad as you traverse.
content.location: This problem starts on the left side of the face with 2 textured slope holds and traverses roughly 12 feet to the right and then tops out. Super easy walk off to the climbers left onto the SHT.

content.description: This is a really cool wall in the postpartum boulders area. The wall is laid back maybe 40 degrees and is super blank, except for the sweet textured holds all along the top lip of it. Since the climbs are friction based you would want cooler temps to have higher chances of sending.
